6 (b) that are exempt under 15-6-225.
7 (4) For the purposes of this section, the following definitions apply:
8 (a) "Biomass generation facilities" means any combination of boilers, generators, associated prime
9 movers, and other associated property, including appurtenant land and improvements and personal property,
10 that are normally operated together to produce electric power from the burning of organic material other than
11 coal, petroleum, natural gas, or any products derived from coal, petroleum, or natural gas, with the use of
12 natural gas or other fuels allowed for ignition and to stabilize boiler operations.
13 (b) (i) "Compressed air energy storage" means the conversion of electrical energy to compressed
14 air by using an electrically powered turbocompressor for storage in vessels designed for that purpose and in the
15 earth, including but not limited to deep saline formations, basalt formations, aquifers, depleted oil or gas
16 reservoirs, abandoned mines, and mined rock cavities.
17 (ii) The term includes the conversion of compressed air into electrical energy by using
18 turboexpander equipment and electrical generation equipment.
19 (c) (i) "Energy storage facilities" means hydroelectric pumped storage property, compressed air
20 energy storage property, regenerative fuel cells, batteries, flywheel storage property, or any combination of
21 energy storage facilities directly connected to the electrical power grid and associated property, appurtenant
22 land and improvements, and personal property that are designed to:
23 (A) receive and store electrical energy as potential energy; and
24 (B) convert the stored energy into electrical energy for sale as an energy commodity or as
25 electricity services to balance energy flow on the electrical power grid in order to maintain a stable transmission
26 grid, including but not limited to frequency regulation ancillary services and frequency control.
27 (ii) The term includes only property that in the aggregate can store at least 0.25 megawatt hour
28 and has a power rating of at least 1 megawatt for a period of at least 0.25 hour.
