4 (d) "Flywheel storage" means a process that stores energy kinetically in the form of a rotating
5 flywheel. Energy stored by the rotating flywheel can be converted to electrical energy through the flywheel's
6 integrated electric generator.
7 (e) "Hydroelectric pumped storage" means a process that converts electrical energy to potential
8 energy by pumping water to a higher elevation, where it can be stored indefinitely and then released to pass
9 through hydraulic turbines and generate electrical energy.
10 (f) (i) "Regenerative fuel cell" means a device that produces hydrogen and oxygen from electricity
11 and water and alternately produces electrical energy and water from stored hydrogen and oxygen.
12 (ii) The term does not include a green hydrogen facility, green hydrogen pipeline, or green
13 hydrogen storage system as defined in 15-6-163.
14 (g) "Wind generation facilities" means any combination of a physically connected wind turbine or
15 turbines, associated prime movers, and other associated property, including appurtenant land and
16 improvements and personal property, that are normally operated together to produce electric power from wind.
17 (5) (a) The department of environmental quality shall determine whether to certify that a
18 transmission line meets the criteria of subsection (1)(x), (1)(y), or (1)(z), as applicable, based on an application
19 provided for in 15-24-3112. The department of environmental quality shall review the certification 10 years after
20 the line is operational, and if the property no longer meets the requirements of subsection (1)(x), (1)(y), or
21 (1)(z), the certification must be revoked.
22 (b) If the department of revenue finds that a certification previously granted was based on an
23 application that the applicant knew was false or fraudulent, the property must be placed in class nine under 15-
24 6-141. If the application was fraudulent, the applicant may be liable for additional taxes, penalty, and interest
25 from the time that the certification was in effect.
26 (6) Class fourteen property is taxed at 3% 6% of its market value."
